track_notes: This route is a ski traverse from the Illecillewait parking lot or from the AO Wheeler Hut. You will follow the route to the Illecillewait Glacier and access the glacier from the toe, choosing the best route between crevasses.  Once you are on the glacier, you will head for Lookout Col where you will access the ridge that takes you to the summit of Youngs Peak.  The summit block conditions may necessitate boot packing to the summit.  From the summit, you can choose to ski down the Seven Steps of Paradise to the Asulkan River drainage, or you may choose to drop down to the Asulkan Hut and access the Tree Triangle down to the Asulkan River Drainage.  This track does not show the down track but both options will be obvious from the summit.  The Asulkan River drainage will eventually meet up with your up-route above the old Glacier House Ruins.

If you choose to climb Youngs Peak from the Asulkan Hut, you may follow the Asulkan River all the way up to the Moustrap, then choose whether to go up the moraine or through the tree triangle to the hut.  This route goes through the tree triangle which is usually the safer option with respect to avalanche risk.  You will end up approaching the hut through the gully below the hut.  From the hut, you make your way through various formations, heading to climbers right of the main face of Youngs Peak.  Keep to the right to avoid avalanche exposure steeply up the face to a sloping ridge that leads to the summit.  Excellent cell phone reception is available at the summit.  Note, this trip puts one in avalanche terrain, sometimes on slopes more than 45 degrees so proper preparation is in order.
